comments.content: This looks like something [Identikal](http://web.archive.org/web/20051111043625/http:/www.identikalshop.com/font_search.php?searchTypeID=1&foundrySubSection=name) might’ve done, but I couldn’t find it in their collection.

Yes looks like their work (wich, by the way, is very interesting)…

Unfortunely, I tried all the fonts and none has that kind of “Y”…

Let’s wait for other members to try to id it…

Thanks anyway!!

(Hey, aren’t you Yves?)

Jorge Marcedo  
Coimbra | Portugal

Maybe a custom type by Sven Kils for his current portfolio, and used on his client ID/site.

[http://www.konstruct.de/issue\_03/](http://web.archive.org/web/20051111043625/http:/www.konstruct.de/issue_03/)

Adriano, I found that link here in another post and pick this work up but can’t ID the font used by him… May be you’re right, because Sven works with type designers!
